de.htwg_konstanz.ebus.framework.wholesaler.api.boa
Class CurrencyBOA

java.lang.Object
  de.htwg_konstanz.ebus.framework.wholesaler.api.boa.CurrencyBOA

public class CurrencyBOA
extends java.lang.Object

The CurrencyBOA provides common CRUD operations (Create Read Update Delete) for the currency entity.

The business object BOCurrency represents a currency entity with it's common attributes like code and description.

The following example code shows how to create and persist a new currency entity using the CurrencyBOA. 

 // create the currency
 BOCurrency currency = new BOCurrency();
 currency.setCode(TEST_CURRENCY_CODE);
 currency.setDescription(TEST_CURRENCY_DESCR);
 CurrencyBOA.getInstance().saveOrUpdate(currency);
The following example code shows how to load an existing currency entity, using the CurrencyBOA. 
 // load the currency
 BOCurrency currency = CurrencyBOA.getInstance().findCurrency(TEST_CURRENCY_CODE);
The following example code shows how to load and update an existing currency entity, using the CurrencyBOA. 
 // load the currency
 BOCurrency currency = CurrencyBOA.getInstance().findCurrency(TEST_CURRENCY_CODE);
 if (currency != null)
 {              
        // change the currency description
        currency.setDescription(TEST_CURRENCY_UPDATED_DESCR);
        CurrencyBOA.getInstance().saveOrUpdate(currency);
 }
The following example code shows how to delete an existing currency entity, using the CurrencyBOA. 
 // load the currency
 BOCurrency currency = CurrencyBOA.getInstance().findCurrency(TEST_CURRENCY_CODE);
 if (currency != null)
 {              
        // delete the currency
        CurrencyBOA.getInstance().delete(currency);
 }
